reviews.review_text: This small little gem was the perfect spot for a Vegan/ Carnivore duo to dine together.  I had the cornbread with pulled pork and it was so delicious.  The bread was just the right amount of crisp and crunch around the edges, moist and full of flavor.  The presentation of the food was too pretty to not capture the memory and everything else about the meal and drinks was above average.  Even their grapefruit juice was better than I ve had and noteworthy! Having our server interact with us throughout the entire meal added to the fun.  He even sat with us for a few minutes for conversation as he cheered us on to try our first ever pickle back. Great experience and a shout out to our camera shy server that we would ask for by name if only I could remember it!

Amazing vegan wings. Immediately after finishing i already planned a return visit. I recommend the Valentina hot sauce with ranch dip (all vegan).  Would love to see more vegan options like cornbread or Mac and cheese

We came here after a team building event. It was fantastic and friendly service and the food was delicious! It was a very hot day and we chose to sit inside because their outdoor area is in the back and smelled very strongly of garbage. The inside doesnt have AC so it was prettttyyyyy slick inside too. They have some cool rolling windows which they opened and that helped a bit. The food and service way outweighed the issues with the location. Highly reccomend!

Awesome BBQ! The brisket and ribs are very tasty. Staff were very friendly. The Mac and cheese was the highlight for sure, if you like spice you will love it! We had the banana pudding for dessert, prefect thing to share after dinner. The coleslaw was not my favourite. Would definitely recommend this place!

Im gonna go ahead and say that slims have the best nachos in vancouver. No soggy chips and no burnt cheese that we see everywhere else. Tasty cheese sauce, crispy tortilla chips. 10/10. And their happy hour couldnt be better. Slims is it.
Just a fantastic little place. What makes it even better is Cobra Lynn! Love that woman. She made the whole experience even better and well absolutely be back next time Im back in Van.
Love this place! So friendly and amazing comfort food. They do Brunch now which is a must have!

Accompanied by my BFF, two famished mortals were seeking the ultimate humble feast experience and Slims was recommended by a friend. An hour after our culinary coup the two mortals left Slims totally smitten. Next time, and there will be one, were going to request sleeping bags to sleep over for the following days menu. Thanks to the stellar crew of Goddesses & a God for making mortals feel at home. Cheers

Came for brunch. The server/bartender was very attentive and offered us some beer samples when we were unsure without hesitating. Ordered the cornbread and pulled pork, absolutely delicious. Reasonably priced ($15 for a good portion with proper hash browns), and the beer on tap was affordable too. Perfect place to come when hungover for a greasy meal and a pint!
The BBQ was really good. The Mac & cheese was a bit on the spicy side for me. Brisket and ribs were F ing  delicious! Banana pudding topped it all off nicely!
A cute place with really good food! We received excellent service from Bella!

Try their Jalapeno Mac n Cheese with pulled pork (love the extra kick). The beauty of its facade comes from its no-frills decor.  Good portions of comfort food + drinks = perfect for summer.  Tip: They have a hidden patio

Just stopped here for a late lunch after the Squamish marathon and it was the perfect place to wind down and get a hefty meal in. The atmosphere is very chill, service was very friendly and fast, and the food was awesome! The portions were also so much bigger than expected. Also awesome that they re so accommodating to dietary restrictions (lots of veggie, vegan, and GF options). The whole reason we stopped here was because of the sign out front saying they re friendly for vegans and carnivores! Thanks guys we will definitely be back!

Great experience here, majority of the menu can be made gluten free! We had their happy hour tacos and wine which tasted great. Off the regular menu, we had their brisket (which runs out relatively quick) and Nashville fried chicken sandwich (also gluten free) which also tasted great. Great to have another gluten aware/friendly restaurant in Vancouver. The service was also very accommodating and friendly. Dietary restrictions: Gluten free options and celiac friendly although not a gluten free restaurant.
Great server, nice to sit at the back patio, great food, reasonably priced

Slims was great! We (as a group of three) tried a whole variety of things on the menu, and the fried chicken, corn bread and shrimp po boy were my personal faves, though the sides were all tasty. The flavours and spice profiles were balanced and all very more-ish. The staff were fun and engaging as well. Well be going back soon!

When we walked into this unassuming place, we were treated like old friends.   There are plenty regulars there but as first timers, this wont be our last.   We started off with the salt n pepper chicken wings.   The seasoning was so delicious I was sure there was another spice.  The cook said there wasnt, they were smoked.  Husband had the brisket sandwich and I had the pork ribs.   Felt like I was back home at a family BBQ.  Tender and full of flavor.   Great service, great food.  We are hooked
Giant portion for its price, delicious food and friendly staff. They have free pads and tempons in their washroom. Very supportive.

I enjoyed my time at Slims. Its got an old school Main Street vibe, staff are friendly and enthusiastic, good food and drinks. Priced fairly too I think. Its much more interesting to dine here instead of some swanky beige restaurant not too far away. Support your local watering hole!

This was a perfect place for me and my friend to dine together without any one of us compromising on eating or not eating meat. Great coffee, awesome brunch options and a nice cozy spot where you don t feel like you don t belong :) Will come back again for sure!

These lovely humans won me over too quick! Not my usual vibe but hot-dam! The friendliest folks in vancouver: staff and patron a like. Im now a regular and feel warm welcome from all, weekly! Foods good, prices are great, service is unbelievable! I see you cool cat in and hour

Had an amazing time at Slims. Jefferson came out and served us from behind the bar and he was a delight. Very knowledgeable about the menu, and very happy to be there. We had both classic BBQ and the vegan takes on a couple of dishes, and everything was incredible. The cornbread especially made me yearn for the Roe v Wade era American south.
Oh man!! Love this place. Been multiple times in the last few months, trying different menu items and all have been fantastic. Service is top-notch, being friendly and attentive. Food : 5/5
I just had a burger from the late night menu, that will haunt me until I ll come back :D great atmosphere, excellent service, unbelievable food - they d deserve 10 stars!!

This place is amazing,  we try a little bit of everything the only thing we couldnt try was the Beef Brisket because wasnt ready until 5pm but I will try it one of these days I I let you know my people
Every bite of food was delicious. I keep being disappointed eating in Vancouver but not here. Would 100% recommend and will be back.

I came here on a whim with my husband and another couple and I was so pleasantly surprised. Our server (who was also bartending at the time) was attentive and courteous. The food was well priced and as a vegan I was delighted to have multiple options to choose from. I ended up having the Cauliflower to start and the vegan chicken burger for dinner, both were awesome. I especially loved the dark sauce that came with the chicken burger, it was so flavorful. My husband had a brisket sandwich which was tasty, high quality and more food than he expected for the price. We left feeling full (hurray for big portions) and satisfied. We will definitely be coming back.
Stumbled on the place walking back to our condo , great food ( the bubba is amazing ) and good service . What more could u want
Staff are great. Excellent neighbourhood bar for a chill drink.  Ask for a 2 step
Have been there for brunch twice in the last month. Really friendly and accommodating service. We had a toddler with us, and they were great. Food was great too!

Such friendly & attentive staff, and phenomenal food!    Highly recommend the chicharron, corn salad, and the brisket. And to anyone gluten-free: my mom is celiac and I m gluten intolerant, and we felt so safe eating here! Check it out if you can :)
Great brunch, lovely service. There were a lot of vegan and carnivore options, along with endless coffee. All this at an affordable price.

Went here with some family and friends recently and my experience was excellent. The wings, brisket, and mac n cheese were delicious and memorable. One of the best Vancouver rib houses. 10/10 would recommend

We went right when it opened, so we had the restaurant to ourselves. The staff were friendly and helped with my allergy concerns. They do have gluten free options and its all delicious! The fact that its also reasonably priced makes it even more appealing! What a great find- will definitely be back. Dietary restrictions: They cater to gluten free diets- I am not sure about any others.

Not since the advent of the Narrow bar have i been so pleased with a local haunt. A buddy and i came in on a whim. First eye catcher was $7 tap beers! Even the local craft beer purveyors are charging $9for these same beers??? Then, the bbq menu is so deeeelish and i had a dandy pull pork sammy for $14 bucks with salad... Seriously!?? So many F&B places have lost perspective on value. The heat level was kept warm so you actually feel you can stay before hypothermia sets in. Music is very conducive, the renos are very character oriented. Cozy, very good food, no price gouging... A definite go there!!! (one red flag, give it a rest on 18% tips appearing, its a gawdamn recession, your service is the same, my wallet is thinner, pay your staff better, its not my cross tk bear!!

Had a really good time with a buddy at Slims last night. Tried brisket, ribs, fried chicken, with slaw and tater tots. Have I never had good tots before this night? The melt in my mouth brisket was excellent. Had one giant meaty rib which I thoroughly devoured. Everything much better than I had anticipated, takeout box is safe in my fridge for lunch today. Mood and atmosphere, better music and friendly enthusiastic staff. On the other side is a hidden bar where we spent a few more hours.

The food is out of this world good. One of the best BBQ I have ever had. Ribs are to die for, and Brisket was so on point. Shrimp PoBoy was so so good. I did not order from them before because of some of these random 1 star reviews. I can guarantee those are either competitors or people with no taste. Do yourself a favour and give it a shot, you wont be disappointed. I will be ordering weekly going forward.

Had dinner here Monday night (March 1st) with my partner. The server was super attentive and quick with our orders, the food was ~delicious~ and the atmosphere was excellent, with great decor and great tunes. I had the buttermilk fried chicken sandwich with taters + slaw and my partner had a 1/2lb of brisket. We were both super pleased with both the taste of the food and how quick the kitchen was. We will definitely be going back!

Portions are solid, couldn t finish my plate - brisket was amazing although apparently they only do it Saturdays. We got the server with the moustache and glasses, he was friendly, really on top of making sure we had water/were enjoying the meal, etc., in an appropriate non-pushy way    Poifect. Thanks!

Everything was so tasty, and cooked so well. It might have been because we lucked out going near the end of the night, but the portions were absolutely enormous! Sandwiches were loaded sky high, and everybody had a mountain of tots. Also, the night we were there the server was going through some Radiohead albums which was pretty awesome.

Have been twice and was impressed both times. Brisket was a nice mix of both lean & fattier pieces, and the smoked hot links were absolutely delicious. The sides were great, we particularly enjoyed the creamed spinach (with cheese and a perfect amount of heat), the veggie chili, and the brightness of the coleslaw. Those hot links are seriously great though, I have to stress that. My partner is celiac and we were thrilled to learn that the vast majority of the menu is gluten free! We had fair amount of leftovers, which were just as tasty the next day. The redone bar looks great, its larger but makes better use of the space. Its warm, woody, and has bourbon. I was gonna go 4 stars but holy hell I love smoked sausage, so 5 it is.

Ive seen lots of negativity against this restaurant, but today I grabbed lunch there with my mother. That being said, all of our meals were cooked perfectly and extremely fresh tasting! Lots of flavor within the meat, quicky and a nice fresh bun with the brisket sandwich. Would go back again!
Delicious barbacoa and mezcal margaritas! The staff are super friendly.
Serves BBQ meals and wings. Just tried the wings which were tasty. Bon Appetite!

Im a vegetarian but I went in with an open mind and... I was really happy with the night. Luckily there are a few vegetarian options and better yet, theyve very good. I had a veggie burger and a veggie chilli, my lady had the hot fried chicken sandwich with the tots on the side (which I mostly ate). The food, great, the drinks, great. We both got the sinner down south cocktail and I may have topped off my evening with a couple PBRs. The space is great - I didnt feel like leaving. All in all, I never really write reviews but want other veggies to know theyve got options here. We will be back soon.

We ordered the Bubba ($49) which is easily enough for 2 people and a side of brisket beans. Has all the meats and they were all tender, juicy and had nice smoky flavour. Its all a fair deal for what you get. Compared to other smoked places in the city. Cool laid back bar. Small and intimate. Good music.
Amazing...great food at extremely affordable prices...staff is very friendly.

All of the BBQ was amazing, yummy cornbread. Perfect dog friendly patio for watching the sunset. And delightfully charming service. Will be back for sure! Also, the Mount Pleasant Lemonade hit the spot :).
Great service and food! They drink selection is varied, and their food platters are a must-have, amazing corn bread

Good food and atmosphere! The serano spinach and hot links are top items, generous portions for a good price, definitely taking leftovers home. The bar has a good and reasonably priced bourbon selection! Worth checking out in Mount Pleasant!

Slims BBQ is one of the best restaurants I have ever ordered from! My favorite item on the menu is their cornbread with jalapeno butter. It is fantastically scrumptious! Theyre macaroni and cheese is also a big winner with me... And if you like chicken on a bun their double breaded chicken Sammie... YUM!
Great food and service from Cash my bartender good food and vibes.
I m vegan and I love it here! Such a great place to go with my non-vegan friends, and the vegan options are actually SO GOOD. 10/10 would recommend
Went with some friends got the crazy train IPA and nashville chicken sandwich. Delicious food, great ambience and very friendly staff with a great taste in wristwatches! Thanks for a great time!
Reasonable price, good vibes and food.
Slims BBQ is amazing and food here outstanding highly recommended

Hands down best BBQ in the region. Have been trying them all since a trip to Louisiana last year...this is definitely the winner. Perfectly cooked meet, not drowning in sauce. Even the sides were great!

We had such an amazing experience here last night! The staff were fantastic, the drinks amazing and the food was incredible! Highly recommend adding Slim s to you must visit restaurants in Vancouver!!
Been here a handful of times now. Always great service, good food and drinks. Going to miss the brisket baked beans, so good! Will be back again soon!
Tacos! Great! Drinks! GREAT!! very friendly staff, clean bar, FRIED BOLOGNA SAMMIE! WOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!
Best beef brisket Ive had since I was in Georgia. If mustard isnt your jam ask for it light. But I loved it. Looking forward to coming back and trying everything elsr
Chill vibes n good vegan breakfast tacos
Delicious meats and sauces, ideal sharing platters with great variety.
Great staff, great cocktails, great ambiance and great food. This new restaurant is definitely worth your time and appreciation. Bold move to open a new spot during a pandemic.
Awesome
Great BBQ and awesome drinks!!! We came on Friday just after 5pm which coincidentally was also the same time the brisket arrived from their smoking kitchen!! OMG... Just do it!!
A great hang out spot - I was a customer when it was the Rumpus Room and Ive continued going. Fun interior, tasty food, and good service.
Very tasty food. Great beer and atmosphere.
delicious BBQ, the brisket is a must try. Great drinks as well. Reasonably priced. Good service
Decent Happy Hour. $4 PBR, $12 brisket sandwich. Service was pronto and attentive.
Such a great bbq platter delicious some of the best smoked pulled pork I ve ever had and the shrimp kisses special was out of this world!
Delicious Food and a variety of beer.
The food is amazing. I will be back.
To give Slims anything less then 5 stars is a travesty. Soul food at its finest. Lovely vibe.
Brisket burger was delight im coming back :)
Good, friendly service and food was amazing.  The shrimp poor boy sandwich was especially great.
The best cold water in town! Girlfriend approved
The pulled pork and tater totes were SO DELICIOUS!
Good happy hour tacos
Great staff and friendly service! I had the po boy (shrimp sandwich) super tasty.
This place is the best. Unbelievable food. Fantastic service. Just awesome
Best coleslaw Ive ever had and Im from the south
Best burger around
This spot gets better every time I go ! Fantastic brisket sandwich!
The chili is fantastic. Spicy...sour cream is recommended!
Great food and great East Van Vibes ($4 PBR)
Great meat & good vibes! Will definitely be back!!
awesome service, dope music, good food
Good food. Decent price. Great experience
If I lived closer Id be there more.
Gotta come to this spot in house! Great ribs and biscuits
Awesome BBQ place for meaty needs.
Great place to East, have fun !!!!
Great spot. Good food and drinks.
Tasty food and cheap beer!
Tots were amazing
nice cornbread.
Awesome food!!
This was very delicious

Really cool Bar atmosphere with a nice trucker spin. Really good Beers and a nice saturdays special with lots of delicious bbq meat and 4 sides. Excellent Coleslaw, Mac and Cheese and Cornbread!  Would recommend 10/10
